'''Wan Long''' (born 1940/41) is a Chinese [[billionaire]] businessman, the chairman and CEO of [[WH Group]], the world's largest pork company, with subsidiaries including [[Smithfield Foods]] in the US.
==Early life== Wan Long was born in China.<ref name="forbes1">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/wan-long/ |title=Wan Long |publisher=Forbes.com |date=1 January 1970 |accessdate=15 June 2017}}</ref>
==Career== In 1968 Wan Long started work for Luohe Meat Products Processing United Factory, and became the factory's general manager in 1984.<ref name="wh-group1">{{cite web|url=http://www.wh-group.com/en/about/leadership.php |title=WH Group Limited - Leadership |publisher=Wh-group.com |date=16 July 2014 |accessdate=15 June 2017}}</ref>
Wan Long is the chairman of [[WH Group]], the world's largest pork company, with subsidiaries including [[Smithfield Foods]] in the US.<ref name="forbes1"/> Wan Long has been chairman since November 2010, and CEO since October 2013.<ref name="wh-group1"/>
==Personal life== Wan Long lives in [[Luohe]], China.<ref name="forbes1"/>
